										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<h1 class="has-text-align-center">Deshalb landen Ihre E-Mails im Spam (und was man dagegen tun kann)</h1>
<div class="post-content-category"><a href="https://sleeknote.com/de/blog/category/unkategorisiert" rel="category tag">Unkategorisiert</a></div>


<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-large"><img width="1024" height="437" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-1024x437.jpg" alt="Why Emails Go to Spam (WordPress)" class="wp-image-90855" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-1024x437.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-300x128.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-768x328.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-1536x656.jpg 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-380x162.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-600x256.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-760x325.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-1440x615.jpg 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-960x410.jpg 960w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-82x35.jpg 82w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-117x50.jpg 117w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-740x316.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-220x94.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress-385x164.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Why-Emails-Go-to-Spam-Wordpress.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>


<div id="preamble-block_5e9826e34bf8c" class="block-preamble"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">E-Mail war und ist ein absolutes Arbeitstier für Marketingspezialisten. Eine Studie der Direct Marketing Association and Demand Metric ergab: &#8222;E-Mails hatten einen <a href="https://www.emarketer.com/Article/Email-Continues-Deliver-Strong-ROI-Value-Marketers/1014461" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">durchschnittlichen ROI von 122 Prozent</a> — mehr als viermal so hoch wie andere Marketingkanäle wie Social Media, Direct Mail und Paid Search&#8220;.</span></p>
</div>






<p>So wird die Arbeit definitiv erledigt.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Aber es gibt ein Problem, mit dem alle E-Mail-Marketingspezialisten zu kämpfen haben, und das fällt in das gefürchtete schwarze Loch, das der Spam-Ordner ist.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Der Deliverability Benchmark Report 2017 von Return Path ergab, dass <a href="https://returnpath.com/downloads/2017-deliverability-benchmark-report/?sfdc=70137000000EUhC" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">20 Prozent</a> aller kommerziellen E-Mails als Spam enden.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="530" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-1024x530.png" alt="Return Path’s 2017 Deliverability Benchmark Report" class="wp-image-90843" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-1024x530.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-300x155.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-768x398.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-380x197.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-600x311.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-760x394.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-68x35.png 68w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-97x50.png 97w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-740x383.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-220x114.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report-385x199.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Return-Path’s-2017-Deliverability-Benchmark-Report.png 1058w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Und seien wir ehrlich. Eine E-Mail ist fast immer verloren an diesem Punkt.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Ich meine, wie viele Leute werden sich tatsächlich die Zeit nehmen, ihren Spam-Ordner zu durchsuchen, um zu sehen, ob Ihre mail eventuell nur versehentlich dorthin umgeleitet wurde?</p>



<p>Meine Schätzung ist gleich Null.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Dies ist äußerst problematisch, da die durchschnittliche Öffnungsrate nur <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/sales/average-email-open-rate-benchmark" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">32 Prozent</a> und für bestimmte Branchen sogar noch niedriger liegt.</p>



<p>Wenn Sie also E-Mails berücksichtigen, die an Spam gehen, nimmt diese Zahl noch weiter ab.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Im Moment werde ich einige allgemeine Gründe besprechen, warum E-Mails zu Spam werden und wie man sicherstellen kann, dass Ihre nicht dort landen.&nbsp;</p>


<div id="contentupgrade-block_5e9961816d77c" class="block-content-upgrade">
    <div class="text">
        <p class="text-pretitle">FREIE RESSOURCEN</p>
